  "prompt": "Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs): What is the fuss in IIT-M Periyar-Ambedkar study circle all about?",
  "response": "The controversy surrounding the Periyar-Ambedkar Study Circle (PASC) at the Indian Institute of Technology Madras (IIT Madras) centers on issues of free speech, academic freedom, and political expression within educational institutions in India. The study circle, named after social reformers E.V. Ramasamy (Periyar) and B.R. Ambedkar, was formed to promote discussions on social justice, caste, and discrimination.\n\nThe fuss began when the administration of IIT Madras took action against the study circle, which was seen by some as an attempt to stifle dissent and limit discussions on contentious social issues. Critics argued that the actions taken against PASC represented a broader crackdown on freedom of expression in Indian universities, especially regarding discussions surrounding caste, social justice, and other pertinent socio-political issues.\n\nSupporters of the study circle emphasized the need for platforms that facilitate dialogue on social issues and defend the rights of marginalized communities. The situation at IIT Madras sparked a nationwide debate about the role of educational institutions in fostering open discourse versus the perceived need for maintaining institutional decorum and order.\n\nOverall, the events at IIT Madras reflected deeper societal tensions regarding caste, politics, and the role of universities in shaping public discourse in India.",
